---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bangladesh Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/bangladesh/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'India for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/india' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Sri Lanka for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/sri-lanka' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bangladeshFit', header: 'Bangladesh Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BDT$53,500-76,400/mo', bangladeshFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BDT$62,600-89,400/mo', bangladeshFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BDT$48,150-68,750/mo', bangladeshFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BDT$44,750-63,900/mo', bangladeshFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (MetLife, Pragati)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'BDT$8,000-20,000/mo', bangladeshFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BDT$48,150-76,400', annual: 'BDT$578K-917K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BDT$66,050-101,900', annual: 'BDT$792.6K-1.22M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BDT$88,800-136,750', annual: 'BDT$1.07M-1.64M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'BDT$2,000-6,000/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'BDT$15,000-40,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bangladesh 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Bangladesh. Delta beauty, very affordable living, limited healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bangladesh"
  subheadline="Bangladesh offers Sundarbans delta beauty, extremely affordable living, warm hospitality, and growing economy—primarily for those with family connections or specific professional reasons."
  heroImage="/images/countries/bangladesh-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Bangladesh</h2>
  <p>
    Bangladesh is primarily chosen by those with family connections or specific professional/development work reasons. Offers extremely low cost of living, warm Bengali hospitality, Sundarbans tiger reserve, and growing economy. Not a typical Western retirement destination but relevant for specific demographics.
  </p>

  <p>
    Dhaka is the capital with best (though still limited) healthcare. Chattogram has second city options. Cox's Bazar offers world's longest beach. Sylhet has tea gardens. Most expats based in Dhaka for healthcare and services.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Bangkok/Singapore evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Bengali; English in business</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BDT$60,000-120,000/month (~$550-1,100 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical monsoon; hot humid; cyclone risk</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Dense; bustling; hospitable</li>
      <li><strong>Target demographic:</strong> Family connections; development work</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Bangladesh Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Bangladesh healthcare is limited—Apollo Hospitals Dhaka and Square Hospitals are best private options. Quality improving but limited specialists. Complex cases typically evacuate to Bangkok (2.5-hour flight) or Singapore. International insurance with evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare in Dhaka is affordable. Public system underfunded. Medical tourism to Thailand/Singapore common. International insurance with strong regional coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Regional Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bangladesh healthcare is limited for complex conditions. Bangkok (2.5 hours) and Singapore (4 hours) provide excellent backup. Include Thailand/Singapore in insurance coverage. Don't rely solely on local healthcare for serious conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Bangladesh visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-90 days available. Apply through embassy or e-visa where available.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For business activities. Various categories with different durations.
  </p>

  <h3>Multiple Entry Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For frequent visitors. Good for those with family connections.
  </p>

  <h3>No Formal Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    No specific retirement program. Long-term stays require appropriate visa category.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Bangladesh:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Thailand/Singapore coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Consider cyclone/flood coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Bangladesh</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Thailand/Singapore evacuation coverage essential. Dhaka private hospitals handle routine care. Regional hubs provide specialist backup. Don't economize on evacuation coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Bangladesh, regional evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Bangladesh</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, Bangkok access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Thailand access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore backup:</strong> World-class healthcare option</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Asia-Pacific evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Bangladesh (BDT ~109 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dhaka base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Bangkok network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Family support:</strong> Local connections help navigation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Returning Bangladeshi-American, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Family in Dhaka. Extended visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with US and Asia coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BDT$58,000/month (~$530). Family connection; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Development Worker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month income. NGO work. Dhaka based.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with strong evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BDT$65,000/month (~$595). Professional work; global coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British-Bangladeshi Retiree, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,000/month pension. Split time UK/Bangladesh.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with UK and Asia coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BDT$55,000/month (~$505). Dual residence; comprehensive.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bangladesh safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—low violent crime against foreigners. Political demonstrations occur. Traffic is chaotic and dangerous. Avoid crowded areas during political events. Normal precautions apply. Not dangerous but challenging environment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Bengali?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—Bengali is primary language. English spoken in business, healthcare, educated class. Without Bengali, life is more challenging. Family/professional connections help navigate. Learning basics valuable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why would a senior choose Bangladesh?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Family connections—Bangladeshi diaspora returning/visiting family. Development work—NGO and international organization presence. Cultural heritage—reconnecting with roots. Extremely low cost—budget maximization. Not typical Western retirement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about climate challenges?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Real concerns—tropical monsoon climate, hot and humid. Flooding during monsoon. Cyclone risk in coastal areas. Air quality issues in Dhaka. Climate change impacts significant. May be challenging for seniors with respiratory conditions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Bangladesh coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Bangladesh is primarily suitable for those with family connections or specific professional reasons. Always verify current requirements and conditions before travel.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
